<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Type-Safety on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/type-safety/</link><description>Recent content in Type-Safety on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/type-safety/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::bad_any_cast - any_cast failure</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/any-cast-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/any-cast-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="stdbad_any_cast---any_cast-failure"&gt;std::bad_any_cast - any_cast failure&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;std::bad_any_cast&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when &lt;code&gt;std::any_cast&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; is used to extract a value of a different type than what was stored.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Wrong type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;any a &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string s &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;any_cast&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(a); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Empty any
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;any a;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;any_cast&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(a); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Pointer cast on value
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;any a &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;any_cast&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;a); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// returns nullptr, doesn&amp;#39;t throw
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-type-first"&gt;Fix 1: Check type first&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;any a &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; get_value();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (a.type() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;typeid&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;)) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;any_cast&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(a);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-pointer-cast"&gt;Fix 2: Use pointer cast&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;any_cast&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;a)) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;p;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Wrong type&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-has_value"&gt;Fix 3: Use has_value&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (a.has_value()) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;any_cast&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(a);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;bad_any_cast&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Type mismatch&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-cast-dynamic/"&gt;std::bad_cast&lt;/a&gt; — dynamic_cast failure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-variant-access/"&gt;std::bad_variant_access&lt;/a&gt; — wrong variant type.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-optional-access/"&gt;std::bad_optional_access&lt;/a&gt; — empty optional.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::bad_variant_access — Variant Type Mismatch Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-variant-access-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-variant-access-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdbad_variant_access--variant-type-mismatch-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::bad_variant_access — Variant Type Mismatch Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::bad_variant_access&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when &lt;code&gt;std::get&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;()&lt;/code&gt; is called on a &lt;code&gt;std::variant&lt;/code&gt; that does not currently hold a value of type &lt;code&gt;T&lt;/code&gt;. This commonly happens when code assumes a variant holds a specific type without checking first. The exception also occurs when accessing a variant that is valueless by exception.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdbad_variant_access-occurs"&gt;Why std::bad_variant_access Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include calling &lt;code&gt;std::get&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; without first checking &lt;code&gt;std::holds_alternative&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;, a variant becoming valueless after a throwing assignment, and using &lt;code&gt;std::get&lt;/code&gt; on a variant returned from a function that may hold any of its alternative types.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::variant Error — Variant Access Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/variant-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/variant-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdvariant-error--variant-access-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::variant Error — Variant Access Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::variant&lt;/code&gt; error occurs when accessing a variant with the wrong type using &lt;code&gt;std::get&lt;/code&gt;, or when the variant is valueless by exception. &lt;code&gt;std::bad_variant_access&lt;/code&gt; is thrown on mismatched type access. Variants can also become valueless after a throwing assignment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdvariant-errors-occur"&gt;Why std::variant Errors Occur&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include calling &lt;code&gt;std::get&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; without checking which type is active, variant becoming valueless after a throwing move constructor, using &lt;code&gt;std::get&lt;/code&gt; on a variant returned from an unknown source, and not handling all alternative types in visitation.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Java ClassCastException: Cannot Be Cast To Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/classcast-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/classcast-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="classcastexception-cannot-be-cast-to"&gt;ClassCastException: Cannot Be Cast To&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ClassCastException&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when you attempt to cast an object to a type it is not an instance of at runtime. Despite Java&amp;rsquo;s compile-time type checking, casts on &lt;code&gt;Object&lt;/code&gt; references, raw collections, and generic type erasure can produce invalid casts that only fail at runtime.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Java enforces type safety at compile time, but some casts bypass the compiler and are validated at runtime. When the actual object type doesn&amp;rsquo;t match the target type, the JVM throws &lt;code&gt;ClassCastException&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Null check operator used on null value</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/frameworks/flutter/flutter-dart-null-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/frameworks/flutter/flutter-dart-null-error/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The &amp;ldquo;null check operator used on null value&amp;rdquo; error occurs in Dart when the &lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt; (bang) operator is applied to a nullable variable that holds &lt;code&gt;null&lt;/code&gt; at runtime. This is a common error in Flutter apps that have not fully adopted null safety or use &lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt; without null checks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt; on a nullable variable without checking for null first&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Widget &lt;code&gt;context&lt;/code&gt; accessed after the widget is disposed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Route arguments accessed without null check&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;State variables not initialized before use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Future results accessed with &lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt; without null check&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Replace &lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt; with null-safe alternatives:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-dart" data-lang="dart"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Bad: null check operator
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; user&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;.name;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Good: null check or default
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; user&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;.name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;??&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Guest&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start="2"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use null checks before accessing:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-dart" data-lang="dart"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (user &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; user&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;.name;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start="3"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use pattern matching (Dart 3+):&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-dart" data-lang="dart"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;switch&lt;/span&gt; (user) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; User() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; user.name,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; _ &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Guest&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;};
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start="4"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely access widget context:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-dart" data-lang="dart"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;@&lt;/span&gt;override
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Widget build(BuildContext context) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; args &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; ModalRoute.of(context)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;.settings.arguments &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; Map&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; id &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; args&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;id&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; Text(id &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;??&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;No ID&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start="5"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initialize state variables properly:&lt;/li&gt;
